Interface TableResolver

    • Method Detail

      • resolve

        URL resolve(String table,
            URL base)
        Resolve a table.
        Parameters:
        table - The table name. Can be a relative or absolute file path, or some other identifier.
        base - If non-null, resolving against this base URL.
        Returns:
        The resolved resource as a URL, or null. If the table can be resolved, it must resolve to exactly one table file. Liblouis supports specifying a comma-separated list of tables, but that feature is not supported via this interface. The returned URL must represent one table file, however that does not mean that the URL must be a file URL. It may be any kind of URL as long as an InputStream is obtained upon calling the openStream() method.

      • list

        Set<String> list()
        List all the available table files. This includes "top-level" tables but also table files intended for inclusion in other tables.
